    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 120 species in six families including shoebills, New World vultures, ibises, and bitterns. They are long-legged wading birds with long bills and feet that are not webbed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
